<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/22786067-mark-vickers">Mark Vickers</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It satisfied me because of the beauty of the writing and eccentricity of the narrator, but it is far from a conventional mystery. If one only reads fo<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It satisfied me because of the beauty of the writing and eccentricity of the narrator, but it is far from a conventional mystery. If one only reads for the mystery plot line, then it's satisfactory but not great. If one reads as a work of art, it's terrific.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
